# Mobile Accessibility - Touch Target Minimum Size

All interactive elements (buttons, checkboxes, links) must have a minimum touch area of **48px × 48px** for mobile accessibility.

## Implementation Pattern

The visual element can remain small, but extend the touch area using padding and negative margins:

```css
/* Example: 24px button with 48px touch area */
.button {
  width: 24px;
  height: 24px;
  /* Extend touch area to 48px */
  padding: 12px;  /* 24 + (12 × 2) = 48px */
  margin: -12px;  /* Negative margin to prevent layout shift */
}

/* Example: 22px checkbox with 48px touch area */
.checkbox {
  width: 22px;
  height: 22px;
  /* Extend touch area to 48px */
  padding: 13px;  /* 22 + (13 × 2) = 48px */
  margin: -13px;
}

/* Example: 30px tag with 48px touch area */
.tag {
  min-width: 30px;
  height: 30px;
  /* Extend touch area to 48px */
  padding: 9px 14px;  /* vertical: 30 + (9 × 2) = 48px */
  margin: -9px -9px;
}
```

## Spacing Considerations

When buttons have expanded touch areas, increase spacing between them to prevent overlapping touch targets:

```css
/* ❌ BAD: Touch areas overlap with 6px gap */
.buttonGroup {
  gap: 6px;
}

/* ✅ GOOD: Adequate spacing with 12px gap */
.buttonGroup {
  gap: 12px;
}
```

## Common Interactive Elements

Apply this pattern to:
- Checkboxes
- Icon buttons (bookmark, expand, close, etc.)
- Filter/tag buttons
- Small action buttons
- Toggle switches
